<br>
I am glad not to be a vending machine, but I share JT's worries that we mages are now reverting to our wilderness days of Kunark/Velious.<br>
<br>
I played a magician because I thought it would be cool to let my summoned pet take the damage whilst I dealt it. In a raid situation, pets aren't always allowed. This takes away half of what being a magician is about. This my friends, sucks.<br>
<br>
With the introduction of pet hold pets are now slightly more useful on raids, however, with their awful dmg output on high end mobs, maybe we should look at a way of fixing this.<br>
Introduce spells such as the wizzy bane spells of velious that could only be used on various dragons or giants. With PoP spells for specialised encounters could be introduced. For example:<br>
<br>
MOB-A is in zone_00. Allow the mage to complete a quest that rewards him with a specially designed pet that gives added dmg output against MOB-A. Make it so the pet is more powerful than your average 'epic' or 60 water pet. This would mean the specialist pet would be more powerful but only useable on a certain race or single mob, like MOB-A.<br>
Like a magician version of sseru bane weapons, except less tedious and actually useful.<br>
The quest shouldnt be stupidly long either, we are playing to have fun afterall.<br>
<br>
There could be a number of quests for varying different PoP mobs. This would add variety into a mages life.<br>
<br>
Also, if we are damage dealers, up our nukes a bit. I'm not asking for 5k nukes, but maybe 1600dmg for 500mana? Not overpowered when you consider wizzies get to nuke for 1625 (or so?) for 450mana with sunstrike at level 60.<br>
<br>
I digress, T-rods have given us a crutch, something we can hold onto and claim as our own, but they were boring as hell and required zero skill. If we could solidly use our pets, pets that could be expanded upon greatly to allow variety and fun, I think it would be great fun to be a magician again.<br>
<br>
If Verant want to remove our main raid skill, they have to replace it.<br>
All classes should be equally valuable, or at least have some value. I can't speak for Beastlord but I can for mages. <br>
This would and could be one way to improve a mages life without overpowering us. <br>
<br>
Verant say they want us as dmg dealers, using our pets, it's time to put their money where their mouth is.<br>
<br>
Remove mana rods completely, it isn't a magicians place nor anyone elses to be a mana battery, it is and always has been a stupid idea that does nothing but cause misery.<br>
<br>
These are merely ideas, do with them with you will.<br>
<br>
<br>
Teenybloke Mungbean<br>
